.TH TWU-CTL 1 "2026-05-07" "0.1.0" "Tumbleweed Updater"
.SH NAME
twu-ctl \- Tumbleweed Updater controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B twu-ctl
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B twu-ctl
is the unprivileged controller component of Tumbleweed Updater.
It checks for and applies system updates on openSUSE Tumbleweed,
returning structured JSON output for consumption by the GUI frontend.
.PP
The
.B apply
command must be invoked via
.BR pkexec (1)
to obtain the necessary root privileges.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Check for available updates using
.BR zypper (8)
and return a JSON object describing the current update state,
including package count, vendor changes, Flatpak updates,
firmware updates (via
.BR fwupdmgr (1)),
and whether a reboot will be required.
.TP
.B apply
Apply pending system updates using
.BR "zypper dup" (8).
Must be run as root via pkexec.
Streams progress output followed by a final JSON result object.
Optionally creates Snapper pre/post snapshots, updates Flatpak apps,
and applies firmware updates via
.BR fwupdmgr (1).
A reboot is always recommended when firmware updates were applied.
.TP
.B refresh
Refresh repository metadata using
.BR "zypper ref" (8).
Must be run as root via pkexec.
.TP
.B enable-unattended
Install a polkit rule granting the invoking user passwordless authorization
for the
.B refresh
and
.B apply
actions only, scoped to that user's local, active session.
Must be run as root via pkexec, which itself requires interactive
authentication once.
Never affects the
.B rollback
action, which always requires interactive authentication.
.TP
.B disable-unattended
Remove the polkit rule installed by
.BR enable-unattended .
Must be run as root via pkexec.
.SH OUTPUT
All commands output a JSON object to stdout.
Progress output during
.B apply
is streamed as plain text lines,
with the final JSON result on the last line.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/TumbleweedUpdaterrc
User configuration file in KConfig INI format.
Controls vendor policy, Snapper integration, Flatpak updates,
fwupd firmware updates, and auto-check interval.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/TumbleweedUpdater/history.log
Update history log in JSONL format (one JSON object per line).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/TumbleweedUpdater/last-check-state.json
Timestamp and result of the most recent successful
.B status
check, shared with
.BR twu-ctl-notify (1)
so the GUI can display an accurate "last checked" time regardless of
whether the check was run interactively or by the background systemd timer.
.TP
.I /etc/polkit-1/rules.d/90-tumbleweedupdater-unattended-<user>.rules
Passwordless authorization rule installed by
.BR enable-unattended ,
removed by
.BR disable-unattended .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tumbleweed-updater (1),
.BR twu-ctl-notify (1),
.BR zypper (8),
.BR snapper (8),
.BR fwupdmgr (1),
.BR pkexec (1)
